<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef9d0905-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s300317"><num value="300317">§ 300317.</num><heading> State</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this division, the term “State” means—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idef9d0906-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s300317/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> a State, the District of Columbia, Puerto Rico, Guam, American Samoa, the Virgin Islands, and the Northern Mariana Islands; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idef9d0907-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s300317/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the Republic of the Marshall Islands, the Federated States of Micronesia, and the Republic of Palau.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idef9d0908-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">(<ref href="/us/pl/113/287/s3">Pub. L. 113–287, § 3</ref>, <date date="2014-12-19">Dec. 19, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/3190">128 Stat. 3190</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
